the Russian government.

00:22.566 --> 00:27.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How does this change our
understanding of the Russia
collusion allegation?

00:27.066 --> 00:31.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: Well, I think
it's fair to say, Judy, that
the White House lost any benefit

00:31.100 --> 00:33.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the doubt that it
could claim on this story.

00:33.233 --> 00:37.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The shoes continue to drop,
like it's a Zappos warehouse
or Imelda Marcos' closet.

00:41.200 --> 00:46.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, it just -- each time,
they're amending their story,
they're appending or extending

00:46.933 --> 00:49.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
their story.

00:49.233 --> 00:54.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so I just think the fact
that there were such denials
and accusations of a Democratic

00:56.266 --> 00:59.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
plot, all of those are gone,
and they stand naked and
they stand exposed as shams.

01:01.800 --> 01:05.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, they were actively
engaged, at least welcoming
Russian involvement in the 2016

01:09.433 --> 01:13.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
election, in behalf of Donald
Trump against Hillary Clinton.

01:13.133 --> 01:17.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: David, does
this change your assessment of
what may have been going on?

01:17.066 --> 01:19.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DAVID BROOKS: Yes.

01:19.166 --> 01:22.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
My colleague Ross Douthat wrote
that any time you give Donald
Trump the benefit of the doubt,

01:22.233 --> 01:23.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
he always lets you down.

01:23.500 --> 01:24.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

01:24.500 --> 01:26.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: And that's true.

01:26.566 --> 01:29.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's true for his business
clients and it's true for those
of us who thought, they couldn't

01:29.700 --> 01:34.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have been some stupid, to
walk right into collusion
with the Russian meetings.

01:34.533 --> 01:38.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And yet they were not only that
stupid, but I think what is
striking to me is the complete

01:38.733 --> 01:43.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
amorality of it, that Donald
Trump Jr. gets an e-mail saying
the Russian government is

01:44.966 --> 01:47.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
offering you this, and
he says, "I love it."

01:47.033 --> 01:50.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it reminded me so much
of some of the e-mails that
came out of the Jack Abramoff

01:50.066 --> 01:54.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
scandal, that came out of the
financial crisis scandal, where
they're just -- they're like

01:54.066 --> 01:59.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
frat boys who are gleefully
going against the law and are
going against all morality.

02:00.466 --> 02:03.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And they're not even overcoming
any scruples to do this.

02:03.500 --> 02:05.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're just having fun with it.

02:05.600 --> 02:10.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then, in the days since,
we have had on - - Donald Jr.
on Sean Hannity's show, again,

02:12.066 --> 02:14.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I did nothing wrong, just
incapable of seeing that there
might have been something wrong

02:14.933 --> 02:17.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
about colluding with a foreign
power who is hostile with you.

02:17.733 --> 02:22.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then Donald Trump himself
saying, he's a wonderful guy,
again, not seeing anything

02:22.166 --> 02:26.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
wrong, and then even last day
lying about how many people were
in the meeting, a completely

02:26.500 --> 02:28.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
inconsequential lie.

02:28.566 --> 02:33.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so we're trapped in the
zone just beyond any ethical
scruple, where it's all about

02:33.233 --> 02:35.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
winning.

02:35.233 --> 02:37.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Beyond any
ethical scruple, Mark,
is that where we are?

02:37.833 --> 02:42.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: Yes, I think
it's fair to say that
Donald Trump was born
without the embarrassment

02:43.433 --> 02:45.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
gene or the moral
reservation gene.

02:45.466 --> 02:49.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He just -- he doesn't --
when he says that most people
would take that meeting, Judy,

02:49.733 --> 02:54.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, this is not -- I have
been around for a while, and
been to the Dallas Fair twice,

02:55.533 --> 02:57.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and all the rest of it.

02:57.800 --> 02:59.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
People wouldn't do that.

02:59.966 --> 03:04.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In 2000, Al Gore's campaign
got ahold of, was delivered
George Bush's briefing book.

03:07.300 --> 03:09.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They turned it over to the FBI.

03:09.733 --> 03:12.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's what you do when
you're honorable in politics.

03:12.533 --> 03:14.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This isn't a meeting
with a foreign power.

03:14.100 --> 03:16.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This isn't Canada or the
Swiss Family Robinson.

03:16.933 --> 03:18.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
This is Russia.

03:18.933 --> 03:23.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is a country that has
supported, propped up the worst
of anti-democratic regimes in

03:23.433 --> 03:28.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Middle East, that has
practiced -- mistreated
its own press, mistreated
its own civil society,

03:31.333 --> 03:36.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and economic intimidation
of its neighbors, including
invasion of its neighbors.

03:38.266 --> 03:42.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, this is the one country
on the face of the earth with
the capacity to obliterate

03:42.266 --> 03:43.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the United States.

03:43.800 --> 03:45.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is serious stuff.

03:45.900 --> 03:50.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And to do it so casually and,
as David said, without moral
reservation, is -- I guess it

03:53.766 --> 03:55.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
should be stunning,
but, sadly, it isn't.

03:55.900 --> 03:59.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But some of the
Trump team, David, in their
response to this are sounding

03:59.300 --> 04:03.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
