would even think that they
were doing something wrong.

04:03.133 --> 04:06.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Yes, well, they
just don't -- they don't get it.

04:06.033 --> 04:09.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
My pal Mike Gerson had a good
line in his column today.

04:09.933 --> 04:12.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
If you make losing a sin, you
make cheating a sacrament.

04:12.866 --> 04:14.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And that is true.

04:14.933 --> 04:18.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If it's all win-loss, then
you do whatever you can to win
and to make money and to beat

04:18.900 --> 04:20.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the deal.

04:20.933 --> 04:23.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so I do think you have
entered the zone where they
don't quite see what they have

04:23.133 --> 04:25.166 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
done wrong.

04:25.166 --> 04:29.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But cheating with a foreign
company -- country is -- as Mark
keeps saying, is a grave sin.

04:31.633 --> 04:36.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
